<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881018-0061 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief -- Amax Inc.: Unit Completes Acquisition Of Quantum Chemical Line </HL><SO> </SO><CO> AMX CUE </CO><IN> LNG PET TNM </IN><TEXT>   A unit of Amax Inc. said it completed the purchase of the oil and gas exploration and production business of Quantum Chemical Corp. for $118 million.    Amax, a New York-based mineral and energy concern, made the purchase through its Amax Oil andamp; Gas Inc. unit. Quantum, also based in New York, is a chemical and propane marketing concern.    The properties of the Quantum unit, SPG Exploration Corp., are principally in Texas and Oklahoma. They include interests in about 470 wells with reserves estimated at 130 billion cubic feet of natural gas and 6.2 million barrels of crude oil, condensate and natural gas liquids. It also has interests in three gas processing plants. </TEXT></DOC>